The paper deals with algorithms for local community detection in graphs, which is a topic in both computer science and applied mathematics. The use of conductance as an objective function suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The use of optimization methods and the introduction of a new objective function suggest that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the use of performance guarantees and experimental analysis suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
